 and caring, trenchant and lyric.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  a20th century.  aanarchism.  aart and literature.  acontemporary poetry.  aenglish translation.  aeuropean poetry.  afamous authors.  ahebrew poetry.  ahistorical poetry.  aisrael.  aisraeli poets.  ajudaism.  alife changes.  alit students.  aliterary criticism.  aliterary critics.  alyric poetry.  amoscow.  apoems in translation.  apoetry collection.  apoetry scholars.  apolitical poetry.  apolitical protest.  aprotest poems.  arussian poets.  asiberia.  asocial protest.  atel aviv.  aworld poets.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093668340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520936683423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520936683/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles